{Color 08}Argath{Newline}
{Color 00}My own house was once respected as{Newline}
highly as House Beoulve, you know.
{MClose}
At least, until my grandfather was captured{Newline}
during the war.{Newline}
{Newline}
He turned traitor, thinking to buy his freedom{Newline}
with the lives of his friends.{Newline}
{Newline}
But his freedom scarce outlived his honor.{Newline}
He was not a dozen paces out their gate{Newline}
when the dagger found his back.{Newline}
Killed by some common squire, no more a{Newline}
knight than I.{Newline}
{Newline}
One of the men he betrayed later escaped{Newline}
and spread word of his misdeeds.{Newline}
{Newline}
My lord father would have none of it, of course.{Newline}
But he was the only one. Our bannermen{Newline}
deserted us, our reputation ruined.
{MClose}
I suppose I had best remember my place.{Newline}
Your lord brother has no reason to lend{Newline}
ear to pleas from the likes of me.
{MClose}
{Color 08}Tietra Heiral{Newline}
{Color 00}Delita!
{MClose}
