{Color 08}Cardinal Delacroix{Newline}
{Color 00}I see Gaffgarion's sword was no match for{Newline}
his words.{Newline}
Then again, perhaps the fault lies with his{Newline}
adversary. Beoulve blood is not given to{Newline}
spill easily.{Newline}
Even when thinned with that of a courtesan,{Newline}
it would seem.
{MClose}
But enough is enough. Your intrusions overstay{Newline}
their welcome.{Newline}
{Newline}
Leave the auracite, and then leave Lionel.{Newline}
A generous offer, and my last.
{MClose}
{Color 08}{Ramza}{Newline}
{Color 00}Where is Lady Ovelia?
{MClose}
You mean to free her? What then?{Newline}
{Newline}
{Newline}
You've turned your back on your house.{Newline}
A man cannot prosecute a war alone.{Newline}
{Newline}
Forget this bootless struggle. Think you{Newline}
mere -will- enough to see you victorious?{Newline}
{Newline}
Even will needs force, and you have none.
{MClose}
Tell me where the princess is!
{MClose}
Gone to Zeltennia.{Newline}
{Newline}
{Newline}
Her Highness has chosen to accept our hand{Newline}
in aid over yours.
{MClose}
You lie!
{MClose}
Her Highness has taken her first step toward{Newline}
the throne.{Newline}
{Newline}
But she will need a steady hand to guide her,{Newline}
and yours falters. Who better, then, than us{Newline}
to stand at her side?{Newline}
She saw this—why not you? There's no reason{Newline}
you should not join us as well. The thought of{Newline}
besting your brothers holds no allure?{Newline}
We care no less for this world's fate than you.{Newline}
Together we can change Ivalice for the better.
{MClose}
I have no wish to change the world. But{Newline}
nor can I stand by while men suffer and{Newline}
die on the whim of some select few.{Newline}
Do you truly believe you can change the{Newline}
world? Not even I am so naive as that.
{MClose}
Ha ha! Nescient humility from one possessed{Newline}
of such an artefact.{Newline}
{Newline}
That Stone you hold can twist the very{Newline}
weave of nature, to say nothing of the{Newline}
world.{Newline}
Yet I fear my words are wasted on you.{Newline}
Actions speak louder, yes?
{MClose}
{Color 08}Cúchulainn, the Impure{Newline}
{Color 00}You take no pains to hide your wonderment.{Newline}
{Newline}
How I shall delight to watch you die.{Newline}
Each excruciation ecstasy!
{MClose}
{Color 08}{Ramza}{Newline}
{Color 00}This is auracite's sacred power?{Newline}
{Newline}
How can power so vile banish villainy?{Newline}
{Newline}
{Newline}
Surely the cardinal was no greater evil{Newline}
than this!
{MClose}
{Color 08}Cúchulainn, the Impure{Newline}
{Color 00}Behold Lucavi pow'r made manifest!{Newline}
Whose might o'er all Creation once held sway.
{MClose}
The power of the Lucavi?{Newline}
{Newline}
{Newline}
I see only a devil before me! What have you{Newline}
done with the cardinal?
{MClose}
What nonsense this? I am the man himself!{Newline}
{Newline}
{Newline}
