{Color 08}Rapha{Newline}
{Color 00}Grand Duke Barrington has eyes for one thing:{Newline}
the throne of Ivalice.{Newline}
They call him King already—King of the Forge.{Newline}
He fashions ever more and stronger arms, and{Newline}
trains mages enough for all the realm.
{MClose}
{Color 08}{Ramza}{Newline}
{Color 00}His actions are guided from the shadows.{Newline}
{Newline}
There are others—men who promise to{Newline}
eliminate the dukes Larg and Goltanna,{Newline}
and dub the grand duke regent.
{MClose}
And you fight these men, when fighting them{Newline}
means you must be labeled a heretic? Why{Newline}
would you do such a thing?{Newline}
No, that is a silly question. I know the answer.{Newline}
But surely you must realize your efforts will{Newline}
earn you no thanks.
{MClose}
I do not fight for gratitude.{Newline}
{Newline}
{Newline}
I am a Beoulve. I fight for the honor{Newline}
of my name.
{MClose}
I'd not believe that for a moment. You strike{Newline}
me not as the sort of man to fight for things{Newline}
so trite.{Newline}
No, you see evil and injustice before your{Newline}
eyes and cannot turn away. You do not even{Newline}
think to seek reward.
{MClose}
You mistake me for a better man.{Newline}
{Newline}
{Newline}
But we have spoken enough of me.{Newline}
What will you do now? I must make for {Newline}
Riovanes. They hold my sister there.{Newline}
What of you, now that you've escaped? 
{MClose}
I cannot leave. Not without my brother.
{MClose}
There's a quarrel between the two of{Newline}
you, is there not?
{MClose}
He refuses to accept the truth. We were{Newline}
orphaned in the war, you see. We lost our{Newline}
parents, our home—all but our lives.{Newline}
The memories haunt me even now. Climbing{Newline}
mounds of rubble in search of any scrap of food,{Newline}
the air ever thick with death's foul stench...{Newline}
That was the life from which the grand duke{Newline}
spared us. At the time, I thought it sure the{Newline}
gods had sent him.
{MClose}
You were not alone. He erected a great many{Newline}
orphanages in the war's wake. It was a noble{Newline}
gesture of less than noble intent.{Newline}
He wanted assassins. The orphanages gave him{Newline}
a pool of willing young minds, allowing him to{Newline}
select the very best to groom and train.{Newline}
He must have seen some promise in you and{Newline}
your brother.
{MClose}
We Galthenas are the keepers of a sacred{Newline}
art, passed down through the generations.{Newline}
