My brother and I are conduits, I of the{Newline}
heavens and he of the nether. We channel{Newline}
their power through mantra.{Newline}
Grand Duke Barrington desired that power{Newline}
for his own. When our elder refused him, the{Newline}
grand duke put our entire village to the torch.{Newline}
All is grist that comes to that man's mill.{Newline}
If there is a thing he cannot have, he thinks{Newline}
it better that it not exist at all.{Newline}
To imagine the joy he must have felt when{Newline}
he discovered the two of us among the other{Newline}
orphans—it turns my stomach.
{MClose}
So when you learned of all this, you tried{Newline}
to flee...
{MClose}
My brother and I loved the man as{Newline}
though he were our father.{Newline}
{Newline}
But even that did not stop him{Newline}
from...from—!
{MClose}
For a man of his high station to so{Newline}
prey upon the weak—it is not meet.
{MClose}
